claim.claim-text:
1. A method comprising:
receiving data for printing in a laser printer, wherein the data corresponds to a plurality of lines;
selecting, from the data corresponding to the plurality of lines, data corresponding to a subset of the plurality of lines such that the subset of the plurality of lines comprises (i) a top line of the plurality of lines and (ii) one or more subsequent lines of the plurality of lines;
buffering, in a first buffer, the selected data such that the subset of lines are oriented in a first orientation;
buffering, in a second buffer, the selected data such that the subset of lines are oriented in a second orientation that is different from the first orientation;
determining an initial scanning direction of a laser beam while the laser beam is to scan the top line of the plurality of lines;
based on the determined initial scanning direction of the laser beam while the laser beam is to scan the top line of the plurality of lines, selecting the data buffered in one of the first buffer or the second buffer; and
scanning the laser beam in accordance with the data buffered in the selected one of the first buffer or the second buffer;
wherein
while the subset of lines are oriented in the first orientation,
the top line is oriented in a first direction, and
the one or more subsequent lines of the plurality of lines are alternatively oriented in (i) a second direction that is opposite of the first direction and (ii) the first direction, and

while the subset of lines are oriented in the second orientation,
the top line is oriented in the second direction, and
the one or more subsequent lines of the plurality of lines are alternatively oriented in (i) the first direction and (ii) the second direction.

11. An apparatus comprising:
a processing unit configured to
receive data corresponding to a plurality of lines, and
select, from the data corresponding to the plurality of lines, data corresponding to a subset of the plurality of lines, such that the subset of the plurality of lines comprises (i) a top line of the plurality of lines and (ii) one or more subsequent lines of the plurality of lines;

a first buffer configured to buffer the selected data such that the subset of lines are oriented in a first orientation;
a second buffer configured to buffer the selected data such that the subset of lines are oriented in a second orientation that is different from the first orientation;
a detector configured to determine an initial scanning direction of a laser beam while the laser beam is to scan the top line of the plurality of lines;
a selector configured to, based on the determined initial scanning direction of the laser beam, select the data buffered in one of the first buffer or the second buffer; and
a laser generation unit configured to generate the laser beam in accordance with the data buffered in the selected one of the first buffer or the second buffer;
wherein
while the subset of lines are oriented in the first orientation,
the top line is oriented in a first direction, and
the one or more subsequent lines of the plurality of lines are alternatively oriented in (i) a second direction that is opposite of the first direction and (ii) the first direction, and

while the subset of lines are oriented in the second orientation,
the top line is oriented in the second direction, and
the one or more subsequent lines of the plurality of lines are alternatively oriented in (i) the first direction and (ii) the second direction.
